[SIZE=6][B][COLOR=#00bfff]VelocityNavigator v4.1[/COLOR][/B][/SIZE]
[SIZE=4][I]Premium lobby navigation and intelligent load balancing for Velocity proxies.[/I][/SIZE]
[SIZE=3]Built with ❤️ by [URL='https://github.com/sdemonzdevelopment-spec']DemonZ Development[/URL][/SIZE]

[COLOR=#444444]──────────────────────────────────────────────────[/COLOR]

[SIZE=4][B][COLOR=#00bfff]⚠️ IMPORTANT PLATFORM NOTE[/COLOR][/B][/SIZE]
[B]This is a Velocity-only plugin.[/B] It does not run on Bukkit, Spigot, or Paper backends.
This listing exists for visibility and download discovery. Install the JAR on your [B]Velocity proxy[/B], not your backend servers.

[COLOR=#444444]──────────────────────────────────────────────────[/COLOR]

[IMG]https://raw.githubusercontent.com/sdemonzdevelopment-spec/VelocityNavigator/main/assets/feature-routing.png?v=4[/IMG]

[COLOR=#444444]──────────────────────────────────────────────────[/COLOR]

[SIZE=5][B][COLOR=#00bfff]🧠 v4.1.0 Feature Highlights[/COLOR][/B][/SIZE]

[LIST]
[*][B][COLOR=#00bfff]Bedrock/Geyser Form GUI Support[/COLOR][/B] — Seamless Bedrock player routing with Floodgate UUID mapping, text format stripping, and an interactive, highly-configurable Form GUI popup menu (customize title, body, and button formats via the [I]use_gui_for_lobby[/I] config).
[*][B][COLOR=#00bfff]/vn servers Dashboard[/COLOR][/B] — Paginated lobby diagnostics with CB, drain, and capacity status per server.
[*][B][COLOR=#00bfff]Legacy Color Code Converter[/COLOR][/B] — Auto-detects and converts [B]&[/B] and [B]§[/B] codes to MiniMessage in auto/legacy/minimessage modes.
[*][B][COLOR=#00bfff]Levenshtein Config Validation[/COLOR][/B] — Typo auto-correction with suggestions for all TOML enum settings.
[*][B][COLOR=#00bfff]Self-Documenting Config[/COLOR][/B] — Every config key auto-generates rich comments with wiki anchor links on write/migration.
[*][B][COLOR=#00bfff]First-Run Welcome & Upgrades Digest[/COLOR][/B] — Console welcome dashboard on fresh install, release notes on upgrades.
[*][B][COLOR=#00bfff]Periodic Update Checker[/COLOR][/B] — Scheduled checks with exponential HTTP 429 backoff up to 4 hours.
[*][B][COLOR=#00bfff]Empty Lobby Fallbacks[/COLOR][/B] — Configurable disconnect or fallback_server strategy when all lobbies are unreachable.
[*][B][COLOR=#00bfff]Permission Default Changed[/COLOR][/B] — [B]/lobby[/B] now defaults to [B]"none"[/B] — works out of the box without permission plugins.
[*][B][COLOR=#00bfff]Initial Join Balancing[/COLOR][/B] — Bypasses Velocity's static fallback engine to perfectly split initial proxy connection waves across lobbies before authentication completes.
[*][B][COLOR=#00bfff]7 Load Balancing Algorithms[/COLOR][/B] — Pick the perfect strategy for your network:
[LIST]
[*][B]least_players[/B] - Simple even load distribution (classic).
[*][B]random[/B] - Uniformly random selection.
[*][B]round_robin[/B] - Strict sequential cycling.
[*][B]power_of_two[/B] (Recommended) - Picks two random candidates and routes to the one with fewer players (3-5x better tail latency).
[*][B]weighted_round_robin[/B] - Dynamic, interleaved round-robin respecting individual server weights.
[*][B]least_connections[/B] - Tracks connection EMA (Exponential Moving Average) rates for bursty networks.
[*][B]consistent_hash[/B] - Consistent hashing ring on player UUID for deterministic session affinity.
[/LIST]
[*][B][COLOR=#00bfff]Player Affinity (Sticky Sessions)[/COLOR][/B] — Routes players back to their previously connected lobby with customizable stickiness probability.
[*][B][COLOR=#00bfff]Contextual Routing & Groups[/COLOR][/B] — Segment players to game-specific lobbies based on the server they are leaving (e.g. Skyblock → Skyblock lobbies) with per-group algorithm overrides.
[*][B][COLOR=#00bfff]Automatic Fallback Chains[/COLOR][/B] — Priority-ordered fallback loops when a contextual lobby group is entirely down.
[/LIST]

[COLOR=#444444]──────────────────────────────────────────────────[/COLOR]

[SIZE=5][B][COLOR=#00bfff]🛡️ Network Resilience & HA[/COLOR][/B][/SIZE]

[LIST]
[*][B]Circuit Breaker Pattern[/B] — Monitors and isolates unhealthy servers instantly. Features a full [B]CLOSED ➔ OPEN ➔ HALF_OPEN[/B] state machine to bypass failing nodes before players experience timeouts.
[*][B]Async Health Checks[/B] — Background server pings with configurable timeout and TTL caching.
[*][B]Ping Coalescing[/B] — Merges overlapping pings into a single request, preventing "ping storms" when hundreds of players join at once.
[*][B]Anti-Spam Cooldowns[/B] — Pre-execution locks that prevent macro abuse of lobby commands.
[*][B]Connection Retry & Fallback[/B] — Automatically retries connection attempts on failure, moving down candidate lists dynamically.
[/LIST]

[COLOR=#444444]──────────────────────────────────────────────────[/COLOR]

[SIZE=5][B][COLOR=#00bfff]🔧 Commands & Diagnostics[/COLOR][/B][/SIZE]
[I]All admin commands support tab-completion and require [COLOR=#00bfff]velocitynavigator.admin[/COLOR] permission.[/I]

[LIST]
[*][B]/lobby[/B] (or /hub, /spawn) — Routes the player to the best available lobby.
[*][B]/vn reload[/B] — Live hot-reload of the configuration without restarting the proxy.
[*][B]/vn status[/B] — Premium runtime dashboard showing current strategies, health pools, drain flags, and load distribution.
[*][B]/vn debug player <name>[/B] — Runs a dry-run step-by-step trace showing exactly how the routing engine resolves a player's destination.
[*][B]/vn debug server <name>[/B] — View a detailed health telemetry snapshot of a specific server.
[*][B]/vn drain <server>[/B] — Gracefully empties a lobby server for maintenance. No new connections will be routed to it.
[*][B]/vn undrain <server>[/B] — Resume routing to a previously drained server.
[*][B]/vn drain status[/B] — Lists all currently drained lobby servers.
[*][B]/vn servers[/B] — Show paginated lobby server status dashboard with health, drain, and capacity info.
[*][B]/vn updatecheck[/B] — Manually query for plugin updates.
[/LIST]

[COLOR=#444444]──────────────────────────────────────────────────[/COLOR]

[SIZE=5][B][COLOR=#00bfff]📦 Quick Installation[/COLOR][/B][/SIZE]

[LIST=1]
[*]Install [B]Velocity 3.x[/B] on your proxy.
[*]Place the [B]VelocityNavigator-4.1.0.jar[/B] in your `plugins/` directory.
[*]Start the proxy once — a highly documented [B]navigator.toml[/B] will generate automatically.
[*]Edit the config to specify your lobby servers and preferred strategy.
[*]Run [B]/vn reload[/B] to apply changes!
[/LIST]

[COLOR=#444444]──────────────────────────────────────────────────[/COLOR]

[SIZE=5][B][COLOR=#00bfff]🔑 Permissions[/COLOR][/B][/SIZE]

[LIST]
[*][B]velocitynavigator.use[/B] — Allows use of [COLOR=#00bfff]/lobby[/COLOR] (Default: none, changed in v4.1.0)
[*][B]velocitynavigator.admin[/B] — Access to all administrative diagnostic commands (Default: false)
[*][B]velocitynavigator.bypass.cooldown[/B] — Bypasses lobby command cooldown timer (Default: false)
[/LIST]


